overview: The user tasked the assistant with a comprehensive review and
  implementation of a sleep questionnaire application. The primary goal was to
  ensure the application met the detailed functional and reporting requirements
  outlined in the provided specification. The assistant systematically addressed
  several critical gaps, including integrating a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness with crucial safety warnings, developing detection and
  recommendation logic for complex sleep disorders like COMISA and Insufficient
  Sleep Syndrome, and enhancing the reporting with relevant external resource
  links. Furthermore, the Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring was refined
  to incorporate weighted criteria, and the CSV export functionality was
  significantly upgraded to provide a complete dataset of all questionnaire
  responses. The implementation involved modifications across data types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and both web and PDF report generation
  logic. The conversation concluded with the assistant actively working on
  adding pain severity questions and chronic fatigue screening.
